[32m+[m[32m## Building on Windows[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Install [Flutter for Windows](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/windows). During setup, make sure `flutter` is available from `cmd` or PowerShell.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Install **Visual Studio Build Tools 2022** with the "Desktop development with C++" workload. Flutter requires the Windows C++ toolchain to build desktop apps.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Clone this repository:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```bat[m
[32m+[m[32m   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USER/F-SERVO.git[m
[32m+[m[32m   cd F-SERVO[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Get all assets:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```bat[m
[32m+[m[32m   git submodule update --init --recursive[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   Download additional assets from [here](https://github.com/ArthurHeitmann/F-SERVO/releases/tag/assetsV0.7.0) and extract the folders inside into the `assets` folder. This keeps the raw git repository smaller than 100 MB.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Update dependencies:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```bat[m
[32m+[m[32m   flutter pub get[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Build the Windows executable:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```bat[m
[32m+[m[32m   flutter build windows --release[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m7. The executable will be generated under:[m
